.TH MOPS 1 "April 2026" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mops \- A Lightweight PBS-style Job Scheduler and MLOps Utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mops
\fI<command>\fR [\fI<subcommand>\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mops
is a high-performance C utility for MLOps and DevOps on Linux. It functions as both a lightweight, persistent job scheduling system (a minimalist replica of PBS) and a fast-triage tool for system monitoring. It provides instant feedback on hardware, containers, and the lifecycle of background tasks.
.SH COMMAND MODULES
.B mops
is divided into several subcommands. Use \fBmops <command> \-\-help\fR for module-specific documentation.
.SS worker \- The Scheduler Daemon
Manages the persistent background worker that polls the database and executes queued tasks.
.TP
.B start
Forks and daemonizes the scheduler. The worker will run continuously, polling the database for tasks with a 'QUEUED' status to execute.
.TP
.B stop
Sends a SIGTERM signal to the running worker daemon to shut it down gracefully.
.TP
.B status
Checks if the worker daemon's PID file exists and if the process is currently running.

.SS task \- Job Lifecycle Management
Submits and manages jobs in the scheduler. Provides PBS-style aliases for common commands.
.TP
.B submit, qsub, queue \fI"<cmd>"\fR
Submits a command to the queue. The worker daemon will pick it up for asynchronous execution.
.TP
.B list, qstat
Lists all tracked jobs (queued, running, finished, failed) and their status from the database.
.TP
.B kill, qdel \fI<id>\fR
Sends a SIGTERM signal to a running job's process and updates its status to 'KILLED'.
.TP
.B bg \fI"<cmd>"\fR [\fB\-\-notify\fR \fI<url>\fR]
A lower-level command to immediately run a command as a background daemon without queuing, while still tracking it in the database.
.TP
.B logs \fI<id>\fR [\fB\-\-tail\fR]
Reads or tails the stdout/stderr log file for a specific job ID.
.TP
.B clean [\fB\-\-force\fR]
Scans the process tree for zombie processes and orphaned workers. Use \-\-force to aggressively send SIGKILL to orphaned python/worker nodes.
.PP
\fBOptions for task:\fR
.br
  \fB\-\-notify <url>\fR    Sends a webhook POST on job completion.
.br
  \fB\-\-json\fR           Output in JSON format (for 'list' and 'clean').

.SS disk \- Disk Operations
.TP
.B status
Show disk read/write statistics from /proc/diskstats.
.TP
.B usage
Show total, used, and free space on the root filesystem.
.TP
.B mounts
Display currently mounted drives from /proc/mounts.
.PP
\fBOptions for disk:\fR
.br
  \fB\-h, \-\-json, \-l\fR

.SS sys \- System & Hardware Metrics
.TP
.B cpu, gpu, tpu
Show utilization for hardware components.
.TP
.B oom
List Out-Of-Memory killed processes from dmesg.
.TP
.B cgroup
Show resource limits for the current Docker/cgroup environment.
.PP
\fBOptions for sys:\fR
.br
  \fB\-h, \-\-json, \-l, \-\-pids\fR

.SS net \- Network Operations
.TP
.B port \fI<number>\fR
Finds the process ID (PID) bound to a local TCP port.
.PP
\fBOptions for net:\fR
.br
  \fB\-\-json\fR

.SS gcp \- Google Cloud Platform Utilities
.TP
.B whoami
Instantly print the active Service Account, Project, and Zone.
.TP
.B spot-watch \fB\-\-exec\fR \fI"<cmd>"\fR
Poll for spot termination and execute a command before shutdown.
.TP
.B tunnel \fI<instance>\fR \fI<remote:local>\fR
Establish an IAP tunnel to a private GCP instance.
.TP
.B run-with-secrets \fB\-\-secret=\fI"ENV=NAME"\fR \fI"<cmd>"\fR
Fetch a GCP secret and inject it into a command's environment.
.PP
\fBOptions for gcp:\fR
.br
  \fB\-\-json\fR

.SH WORKFLOW EXAMPLE
.TP
1. Start the scheduler daemon in the background:
.B mops worker start
.TP
2. Submit several long-running Python scripts to the queue:
.B mops task submit "python train_model_a.py"
.br
.B mops qsub "python process_data.py --input /data/large.csv"
.TP
3. Check the status of all jobs in the queue:
.B mops task list
.br
.B mops qstat
.TP
4. Tail the logs of a specific running job:
.B mops task logs 2 --tail
.TP
5. Stop the scheduler daemon:
.B mops worker stop
.SH FILES
.TP
.B mops.db
SQLite database file to track job states.
.TP
.B /tmp/mops_worker.pid
PID file for the background scheduler daemon.
.TP
.B /tmp/mops_task_<id>.log
Standard output/error log files for executed jobs.
